@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - onesubscription/Subscription
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Subscription spec, tracked\nstatus, and delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Use the tracked OCI identity for follow-up\nreconciliation;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListSubscriptions using filters\ncompartment_id, plan_number, subscription_id,\nbuyer_email;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path is not represented by imported\nprovider facts;
:Confirm deletion via ListSubscriptions until\nOCI reaches LOCAL_DELETE;
:Allow best-effort completion without finalizer\nretention;
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartment_id, plan_number,\nsubscription_id, buyer_email and conflicts\nbuyer_email -> plan_number, subscription_id,\nplan_number -> subscription_id, buyer_email,\nsubscription_id -> plan_number, buyer_email;
stop
endif
:Enforce conflictsWith rules buyer_email ->\nplan_number, subscription_id, plan_number ->\nsubscription_id, buyer_email, subscription_id\n-> plan_number, buyer_email before any OCI\nmutation;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nnone;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating;
:Keep promotion blocked on list-lookup;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: onesubscription
slug: subscription
kind: Subscription
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: provisioning, updating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
supported drift: none
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, plan_number, subscription_id,
buyer_email and conflicts buyer_email ->
plan_number, subscription_id, plan_number ->
subscription_id, buyer_email, subscription_id ->
plan_number, buyer_email
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_onesubscription_subscriptions
filters compartment_id, plan_number,
subscription_id, buyer_email
conflicts: buyer_email -> plan_number,
subscription_id, plan_number -> subscription_id,
buyer_email, subscription_id -> plan_number,
buyer_email
open gaps: list-lookup
The published Subscription contract is
query-backed and observe-only. Reconcile issues
ListSubscriptions with compartmentId plus
exactly one of planNumber, subscriptionId, or
buyerEmail, paginates every result page, and
accepts only a single returned summary.
SubscriptionSummary exposes no stable top-level
OCID or reread path. The runtime therefore
leaves status.status.ocid empty and records only
the projected subscription summary fields on the
CR.
The raw subscription status is an untyped
business-state string, not a typed OCI lifecycle
enum. The runtime requeues only clearly
transitional create-like and update-like tokens,
treats FAIL/ERROR values as terminal failure,
and settles all other values as observed
success.
Delete is CR-local unbind only. The controller
releases Kubernetes control immediately and
never calls an OCI delete helper because the
pinned SDK exposes none.
end note
@enduml
